cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NE

The paper proposes a novel in-memory accelerator for matrix-vector-product (MVP)-like operations that find use in traditional and emerging applications. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category, which deals with the design and analysis of computer hardware architectures. Additionally, the paper mentions that the proposed accelerator can accelerate low-precision neural networks, cryptography, and forward error correction, which are all related to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also mentions that the accelerator is fully-digital and can be implemented with standard-cell-based CMOS, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.ET (Embedded Systems) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions that the accelerator can be used to accelerate a wide range of applications and simplifies development, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
